<title>USA: IDX Systems completes merger with Phamis.</title>
<headline>IDX Systems completes merger with Phamis.</headline>
<dateline>BURLINGTON, Vt. 1997-07-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>IDX Systems Corp said Thursday it completed its previously announced merger with Phamis Inc.</p>
<p>&quot;Based on combined 1996 revenues of over $206 million, we believe this merger ranks IDX as the third largest pure play information systems vendor in the health care industry,&quot; said IDX chief executive officer, Richard Tarrant.</p>
<p>In a statement, IDX said the combined company will operate under its name and have 1600 employees.</p>
<p>In 1996, IDX reported revenues of $157.6 million.  Phamis during the same period reported revenues of $49.3 million.</p>
